
runningphotos development log
-----------------------------

Used following options in yeoman fullstack generator:


Write scripts with: Babel
Use Flow types with Babel: no
Write markup with: HTML (as opposed to Pug)
Sass (rather than CSS, Stylus, Less)
uiRouter (not ngRoute)
Included Bootstrap and UI Bootstrap
Mongoose (MongoDB)
Auth template - yes
Using Google, Facebook, Twitter
socket.io - yes
Tests using Mocha + Chai + Sinon
Chai assertions with Expect

----------------------------

To get mongod working:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24599119/mongodb-not-working-error-dbpath-data-db-does-not-exist

sudo mkdir -p /data/db/

sudo chown `id -u` /data/db


----------------------------

npm start


actually, use...

gulp serve

(using npm start resulted in no glyphicons)


---------------------------

Absolutely no idea how, but when initially installing the generator using
npm install -g yo gulp-cli generator-angular-fullstack
I ended up with the alpha version which uses Angular 2.
(confirmed version using npm list generator-angular-fullstack -g which
showed @5.0.0-alpha.3)
Did npm install -g generator-angular-fullstack again and now have
@4.1.1 which is latest stable.

So rebuilt all again using previous options (Babel, etc.)

